New York is a 1976 work of travel and observation by Anthony Burgess. It was written for Timeâ€“Life's The Great Cities series of books. Burgess lived in the city for two years in the early 1970s, teaching literature and creative writing at City College and Columbia University. "New York" is the third single by Eskimo Joe, taken from their third studio album Black Fingernails, Red Wine. The band flew to New York to film the music video for the single. The music video for "New York" debuted on ABC's all night music program, Rage, as the first clip shown on 15 December 2006. "New York" was released on 3 February 2007. The New York Times Magazine is a Sunday magazine supplement included with the Sunday edition of The New York Times. It is host to feature articles longer than those typically in the newspaper and has attracted many notable contributors. The magazine is also noted for its photography, especially relating to fashion and style. The magazine also includes various puzzles, which have been popular features since their introduction.